				<p>Although not directly related to your question, localizing anything with just 3 WiFi routers is a terrible pain. Unless you have some very advanced filtering mechanism up your sleeve, this approach will not work. What can work more easily is to surround your target workspace with multiple routers, probably in a grid, and then log the RSSI signals for all the routers by moving your robot around the area. Train a suitable machine learning algo (ANN might work) in supervised mode to identify the coordinates of your bot, based on the array of RSSI signals. You'll need quite a few routers for this</p>
